text.tspan: COVID-19: Stringency Index, Jan 1, 2020 to Dec 31, 2022
The stringency index is a composite measure based on nine response indicators including school closures,
workplace closures, and travel bans, rescaled to a value from 0 to 100 (100 = strictest).

g.text: Weighted average of vaccinated and non-vaccinated

text.tspan: Data source: Blavatnik School of Government, University of Oxford (2023)
